cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DC 

This paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as it proposes a customizable, application-specific interpretation of activity diagrams. It may also belong to Programming Languages (cs.PL) as it discusses the syntax and semantics of a modeling language. Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) is another possible sub-category as the paper defines a formal semantics for activity diagrams. Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) are also possible sub-categories as activity diagrams are commonly used in these fields.
